# FSD Architecture Rules

Follow Feature-Sliced Design in all production code.

## Layering
- Use FSD layers and dependency direction from lower to higher abstractions.
- Keep `routes` as Next.js page/route analog (project exception).
- Keep tests and test-only shared logic isolated from production code.

## Segment Structure (layers above `shared`)
- `ui`: root exported component and UI-only parts.
- `ui/components`: child UI components used by root component.
- `lib`: reusable local logic (`constants.ts`, `types.ts`, `hooks/`, `utils/`).
- `model`: state, events, selectors, business state transitions.
- `api`: request clients, dto mappers, endpoint bindings.

## Hooks Placement
- Do not colocate component hooks next to component files.
- Place component-related hooks in `lib/hooks`.

## Component File Grouping
- If a component consists of a single file, keep it as a single file.
- If a component has multiple related files (for example `Component.module.scss`, `Component.test.tsx`, stories, fixtures), create a same-name folder and place all related files inside it.
- Exception: root file in `ui` may stay as a file with its related files nearby, without mandatory folder wrapping.
